<br>
Earth...lots more HP than the others, and it roots mobs.  Nice for soloing, and for when you don't want mobs to run away (like in dungeons sometimes).<br>
<br>
Fire...Dmg Sheild, as stated by others. It's much better than your normal dmg shield (you should ALWAYS have a Dmg shield on your pet while fighting solo, by the way).<br>
<br>
Air..stuns mobs, which interupts spell castors.  Nice mellee dmg also.  Good in many good situations, especially if you know you will be fighting spell casting enemies.<br>
<br>
Water..nice mellee pet.  At lvl 54+ they backstab, so are used in small groups or if fear-kiting mobs often.<br>
<br>
<br>
Make sure 1) your pet is always buffed with burnout spell, once you get that spell.   2) your pet always has a dmg sheild on it when fighting mobs solo.   3) you summon your pet armor, once you get those spells. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=draccaviir>Dracca Viir</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.boomspeed.com/apothokeri/staricon.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 193<br> <font color=#333333>(1/22/03 1:36:17 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthelibrary.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=24.topic&index=20>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.boomspeed.com/apothokeri/DraccaPhoto2.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Research for Dracca</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Make sure 1) your pet is always buffed with burnout spell, once you get that spell. 2) your pet always has a dmg sheild on it when fighting mobs solo. 3) you summon your pet armor, once you get those spells.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--> <br>
