  The red gem applies a damage shield to anything you cast it on.  You can cast it on yourself to see how it works first.  When you have a damage shield, anything that hits you gets burns and takes unresistable damage.  You will also notice the damage shield increases your fire resistance.  <br>
  So, always cast a damage shield on your pet.  Every time a mob hits your pet, the mob takes extra damage and dies faster.  You can cast your DS (damage shield) on other players, your pet, yourself.  If you're like me, you will occasionally accidently cast a ds on the mob you are fighting which makes it a lot harder to kill!  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
  The defender spell is only sold in the mage guild in the city of Shadowhaven which is a zone next to the Nexus in Luclin on the moon.<br>
<br>
  The glowing bauble is only sold by the gnome vendor on the balcony of the middle building in the bazaar in Luclin on the moon. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=azzabarr@themagicianstower>Azzabarr</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 41<br> <font color=#333333>(1/22/03 2:01:26 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthelibrary.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=24.topic&index=23>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Misc.</span><hr size=1> Shield of Fire is your first dmg shield spell. Use it and love it.  The spell only lasts for one quick fight, but is well worth the mana to cast it.  Cast it on your pet right before you attack your enemy.<br>
<br>
Elemental defender is a good spell that you should get. It summons a nice shield (for your lvl) that you can give to your pet, so it is better defended.  <br>
<br>
Also, definately get the bauble, bracelet, and ring spells each time you get new ones.   The bracelet makes your nukes do more dmg, the bauble (earring) makes your nukes cost you less mana, and the ring makes you cast spells faster.  Always summon these for yourself when you play.  They will vanish after you camp, so you have to summon them each time you log on.  The bracelet/bauble/ring spells are all sold by the gnome in the bazaar. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=azzabarr@themagicianstower>Azzabarr</A> at: 1/22/03 2:03:29 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=draccaviir>Dracca Viir</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.boomspeed.com/apothokeri/staricon.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 195<br> <font color=#333333>(1/22/03 2:01:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthelibrary.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=24.topic&index=24>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.boomspeed.com/apothokeri/DraccaPhoto2.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Misc.</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>If you're like me, you will occasionally accidently cast a ds on the mob you are fighting which makes it a lot harder to kill!<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
